Barry Lyttle pleaded guilty to causing his brother Patrick to be in a coma with a single punch to the head in Sydney in January . 
  The Irishman could face up to two years in jail after pleading guilty to grievous bodily harm . 
  Patrick Lyttle has called for the charges to be dropped and for his brother to be allowed to return to Ireland . 
  CCTV footage shows the moment Barry punched his brother in the head . 
  Patrick was in a induced coma for six days after the incident . 
  Barry Lyttle could be sentenced for the attack on Thursday . 
 